      • copyAndProcess

        public static void copyAndProcess​(com.intellij.openapi.vfs.VirtualFile from,
                                  com.intellij.openapi.vfs.VirtualFile to,
                                  com.intellij.psi.PsiManager psiManager,
                                  java.util.function.Consumer<com.intellij.psi.PsiFile> fileProcessor)
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Copies a directory and all its contents to another directory.

        After copying, each VirtualFile is converted to a PsiFile using the given PsiManager and passed on to the fileProcessor. The fileProcessor may then edit the tree.

        This method writes files and must therefore be executed inside an IntelliJ write action.

        Implementation adapted from VfsUtil.copyDirectory().

        Parameters:
        from - The directory to copy from
        to - The directory to copy to
        psiManager - The manager to use to convert VirtualFiles to PsiFiles
        fileProcessor - The function to process copied files
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - For generic I/O problems
